Some of the melodies were slightly dissonant, but these types of melodies are often used in jazz as well as rock and work well as long as they connect with other notes previously heard within the sequence. Some of these melodies just had no connection and appeared random, which to the human ear does not sound as if there is any form or pattern that is being followed, and therefore not appealing. I was always looking for a connection within the melodies, something that would make sense or something that would inspire a jump to a new note that would work within the context of the melodic pattern, even if the note is slightly oblique.
